The paper proposes a method for video object segmentation, which is a computer vision task, hence it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method, which suggests that it involves some form of optimization or learning, making it relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The method is applied to videos, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. Finally, the paper proposes a real-time method, which suggests that it may be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
